  <h1>About me</h1>

  <p>I build software products. Operations is where I learned to spot the problems worth building for — years of watching smart people fight workflows that should have been structured, automated, or designed away.</p>

  <p>I started building fixes — first as process improvements, then internal tools, then software products. The constant: I find the gap between how a system <em>should</em> work and how it <em>actually</em> does, and I build the thing that closes it.</p>

  <p>Right now I'm building <a href="/work/budget-itemizer/">Budget Itemizer</a> — a local-first desktop app that turns receipts into YNAB budget splits. It's the kind of tool I wish existed: fast, private, no subscription, no cloud dependency. It runs entirely on your machine.</p>

  <h2>What I bring</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ships real software</strong> — 0→1, working products in people's hands, not mockups</li>
    <li><strong>Owns the product call</strong> — I decide what gets built and why, and carry the outcome</li>
    <li><strong>Finds the ignored problem</strong> — the one people stopped noticing</li>
    <li><strong>Builds under real constraints</strong> — privacy, performance, simplicity as defaults</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>I'm looking for early/0→1 product roles — founding PM, founding designer, early product — where I can own a problem and ship the software for it. If that sounds useful, let's talk.</p>
